                            <comment id="61611" author="linda" created="Mon, 1 Jul 2013 22:33:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changes are ready for review at &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6847/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6847/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="61608" author="linda" created="Mon, 1 Jul 2013 22:01:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removed obsolete note from section 5.2.1:&lt;br/&gt;
Inode size depends on stripe count. Without any stripes an inode allocation of 512 bytes might be sufficient. As striping grows to ~80 stripes per file, the inode allocation is around 2KB. At 160 stripes, a rough estimate for inode allocation is 4.5KB&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
